Impressive. In full transparency I’m doing some research around e-commerce. I’m exploring taking on another side client who embeds extended warranty protection upsells at the time of purchase and takes on all the claim management and insurance for e-commerce stores that sell physical products like electronics, furniture, or things like home goods like Soltech products. It’s impressive. Average shopping carts size increase by 14 percent on average. Higher increase for more expensive checkouts. Furniture and home goods lead the pack.
It’s a “free money” play. All the big e-commerce stores like Best Buy and peloton have it, but this company is targeting smaller e-commerce stores with around $10M in annual sales
I’m doing customer discovery interviews to learn more and understand the obstacles stores face

We have talked about extended warranties before. Definitely something they guys would be open to hearing about. I’ve seen a lot of the chain stores like dicks sporting good use it as an up sell. They push is on almost all their products
